  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; twelve factors meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Model form — carries a required level of 3 but an achieved level of 2. The decision record records Accepted on the basis of compensating evidence from Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, prior regulatory submissions, and expert panel review, but the structural level shortfall for Model form is not formally closed by those arguments.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
